Paul,

I'm sorry this has taken so long, but at last I can get you started.
The following messages represent the new EPROM in binary format.
Bill Chiechi describes this as follows:

	Binary File for HydraMon:
	
	   HYDRAMON.BIN
	
	Hydra EPROM Type:
	
	   Texas Instrumemts, TMS27C040-15JL
	
	Other 150nS, '27C040 compatible devices should work


More software will follow shortly, as well as the answers to your
questions in the FAX and email I have received.

Tim.



